Color

	Philosophy
	
		-
			A color is an object that stores data for an alpha-red-green-blue color.
		-
	
	Principles
		
		Type Section
		
			-
				The child of the type section must have the content "Color".
			-
		
		Data Section
		
			-
				The data section must fields with the aliases "Alpha", "Red", "Green", and "Blue",
				each of which must have a child with a number between zero and one as their
				content.
			-